	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A man died in a tractor incident on a farm in Bethlehem on Thursday afternoon. According to ER24 spokesperson Ineke van Huyssteen, ER24 paramedics stopped on the R56, roughly 8km from Bethlehem, were they were met by a farmer and two workers who transported the patient on the back of a bakkie. "Upon further assessment, paramedics found that the patient was in a critical condition and advanced life support interventions were initiated," Van Huyssteen said. "ER24 transported the patient to hospital but shortly after they arrived at the hospital, the patient succumbed to his injuries and was declared dead." The exact circumstances surrounding the incident were not known to our paramedics, Van Huyssteen said. Safe Driving with Tractors - About 134,000 km from 750,000 km SA Roads are tarred roads... https://t.co/ELpPdaJGX9 #ArriveAlive pic.twitter.com/j2FUSlZRq7  KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  